The malfunction of a Pacific Gas and Electric Co. underground cable left=20
about 5,000 customers, including businesses at San Francisco's Pier 39,=20
without power for more than an hour yesterday afternoon, a company=20
spokeswoman said.=20
A bad underground cable, called a splice, that connects wires was the cause=
=20
